5ï¸âƒ£ What is inheritance and why is it important?
Inheritance means one class can use properties of another class.
It is important because:
Code reuse
Less duplication
Easy maintenance
Better structure

6ï¸âƒ£ Explain any two types of inheritance with real-world examples.
ğŸ”¹ Single Inheritance
One child inherits from one parent.
Example:
Car inherits from Vehicle.
Car gets engine and wheels from Vehicle.
ğŸ”¹ Multiple Inheritance
One child inherits from two parents.
